<p>The International Potato Center, known by its Spanish acronym (CIP), is  an agricultural research-for-development organization dedicated to  achieving food security, well-being, and gender equity for poor root and  tuber farmers, families, and communities.</p>
<p>Founded in 1971, CIP is  headquartered in Lima, Peru, with offices in 40 developing countries  across Asia, Africa, and Latin America. CIP furthers its mission through  rigorous research and innovation in science, technology, and capacity  strengthening.</p>
<p>CIP works with global partners to translate the benefits  of research into sustainable food systems and improved lives. CIP is  part of the global agricultural research alliance known as the <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research (CGIAR)</span>.</p>